<dl id="n12191b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12191b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12191b"> 191(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>law<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> roll in bosom&nbsp;MS</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If we could bring to life the aged brehon of Fermanagh, O&apos;Bristan, of whom Sir John Davies gives us such a tantalising glimpse, <mark>with the old roll in a fair Irish character which he reluctantly drew from out of his bosom</mark>, where he did continually bear it about him, he would solve for us in a few moments problems which the patient toil of an O&apos;Curry, or an O&apos;Donovan, or a Mac Neill has so far failed to unravel. <small> W.F. Butler, &ldquo;Irish Land Tenures&rdquo; <a name="IRLT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IRLT"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (June 1924) 304-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
